    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, so you're saying the deterrence argument is basically just a way to justify social control and keep the status quo? that sounds pretty definitive. isn't there any actual proof that it works for public safety, or is that just a theory used by people who don't care about systemic issues?",
